he wonderful world of Rubika. <br>
<br>
After researching several AO sites and forums, I definately will be siding with the Omni-Tek corporation...mainly to fill my need for a neat looking black helmet &gt;_&gt;.<br>
<br>
The only thing that I've been very undecided upon is what profession/race I'm going to be. I don't exactly want to be  a super ubermegadeathkill profession, but I don't want to be a gimped underpowered one either. I'd like to be pretty useful in a group, have a decent ability to solo (though, I hear that most of the classes in AO have that ability), and fare well in PVP situations. Then there's the most important factor of all...the ability to be efficient with a pair of shiny pistols <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
<br>
Now, I'm not entirely sure, but I think that the Adventurer profession seems to fill my needs in those areas. Advents have healing abilities, some speed nanos, nifty transformation nanos later on, and the ability to use pistols <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  The only negative feedback I got on them was that they were somewhat lacking in the PVP area. Can anyone confirm that? <br>
<br>
Also, the other class that seemed to fit the bill was the Soldier class. Apparently they're the masters of ranged weapons combat and have a variety of different nanos to boost their abilities in combat. Reflect shields, lots of hp, and a perty gun. Plus I hear that they're pretty good in PVP. Opinions on this prof?<br>
<br>
Lastly, I heard *many* good things regarding the agents. Basically the equivalents of rogues in EQ...but with long range sniper rifles and the ability to use the nanos of all the professions. People have also said that they're the most played class and are similar in population to the druids of EQ. This is kind of a turn off for me &gt;_&gt;. *shrug* <br>
<br>
Anyway, those are basically the professions I had in mind. If anyone has any experience with other classes that meet the description I'm looking for, please share. Any information, hints, tips, etc. for an AO newbie would be greatly appreciated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
<br>
Deltiax Hyral<br>
